translations:
‘If you will, you can entrust me with them (pearls, pl.). I
			shall bring them to the city of Baghdad. There are big merchants
			(in Baghdad), and I shall sell them there’ 77/180;

geschieht
			nicht mit der Worfelgabel. Mit einem Korb oder einem feinen Sieb
			hoben wir (das Getreide) in die Höhe’ JL 13.12.12;

“What do you have?” – He said: “Indeed I have lion’s
			milk” – “From where?” – He said: “Now it is for sale.
			Do you want (it)?” 75/316-317;
